{"title": "Creating a New Service Provider Contact", "body": "Creating a New Service Provider Contact\n  Within the Service Providers section of Contacts, MediRecords allows you to create and store new contacts for your system.\nTo create a new service provider contact:\n1. Open the Service Provider Page and click New to open the contact form.\n\n2. You will be shown the New Contact form.\n\n\n\nThe compulsory details to complete are Name, Work Phone, and Provider Type.\n\nTo ensure the new contact has the appropriate privacy setting, configure this in the Sharing field.\nSelect whether you want the contact to be exclusive to you (Private), or accessible to anyone within the practice (Practice).\n\nIf you would like this Service Provider to be used for Pathology or Radiology Requests, please ensure that the Provider Type is set to either Radiology or Pathology. You are then able to assign the provider a template.\n3. Complete the rest of the form as required and click Save.\n\n4. The newly created Service Provider will now appear in your contacts list.\n\nYou should now be able to create a new contact in the Service Providers contacts section of MediRecords. If this is not what you're looking for, head back to our knowledge base and search for another article.\nFor urgent assistance, please contact MediRecords support on 1300 103 903 during business hours."}